Tree Models Lab: Using the Heart Disease or Titanic dataset, train a
DecisionTreeClassifier with no depth limit and observe overfitting. Then apply pre -
pruning by tuning max_depth, min_samples_split, and min_samples_leaf using
GridSearchCV and plot validation curves. Visualise the best tree using plot_tree(). Then
train a RandomForestClassifier with 100 trees and compare accuracy, F1, and AUC -
ROC against the single Decision Tree. Plot a Feature Importance bar chart from both
models. Report OOB error for the Random Forest and compare all results in a final
summary table.
